post_summaries.description: The image shows Chris.d.estes giving a presentation on a stage. He's wearing a grey shirt and jeans, holding a microphone, and gesturing with his hands. Behind him is a projection screen and an American flag. There are people in the audience, and someone is recording him with their phone.

The image shows Chris.d.estes on stage at what appears to be an awards ceremony or conference. He's dressed in a suit and is pointing towards the camera. The backdrop features a geometric design. The caption mentions being recognized as a top earner at NYKO and discusses developing a "championship culture."

The image is a photo of Chris and his wife, Lindsay, celebrating their anniversary. The post describes the importance of intentional effort in marriage and lists six key actions they take to maintain a strong relationship.

The image shows two men in a living room setting. One man is sitting with a laptop, while the other is sitting with a notebook and pen, seemingly engaged in a meeting or planning session. There is an Ironman medal rack in the background.

The image shows a person relaxing by a fire pit in their backyard. The person in the background is smiling and appears to be enjoying the evening. The post includes text about taking a break and refueling.

The image is an Instagram post by chris.d.estes featuring a quote by Jim Rohn: "If you don't like how things are, change it! You're not a tree." The post also includes a personal message from Chris about reflecting on the past year and preparing for the new year using the "3 R's": Reflect, Refuel, Regain Control.
